#########################
###  join filter cost
#########################
explain select /*+leading(A B) use_hash(B) parallel(2) px_join_filter(B)*/* from t1_hash_join A inner join t2_hash_join B on A.c1 = B.c1;
Query Plan
==========================================================================
|ID|OPERATOR                              |NAME    |EST.ROWS|EST.TIME(us)|
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
|0 |PX COORDINATOR                        |        |98010000|0           |
|1 |└─EXCHANGE OUT DISTR                  |:EX10001|98010000|0           |
|2 |  └─SHARED HASH JOIN                  |        |98010000|242150      |
|3 |    ├─JOIN FILTER CREATE              |:RF0000 |1000000 |0           |
|4 |    │ └─EXCHANGE IN DISTR             |        |1000000 |0           |
|5 |    │   └─EXCHANGE OUT DISTR (BC2HOST)|:EX10000|1000000 |0           |
|6 |    │     └─PX BLOCK ITERATOR         |        |1000000 |0           |
|7 |    │       └─TABLE FULL SCAN         |A       |1000000 |0           |
|8 |    └─JOIN FILTER USE                 |:RF0000 |1270000 |0           |
|9 |      └─PX BLOCK ITERATOR             |        |1270000 |0           |
|10|        └─TABLE FULL SCAN             |B       |1270000 |0           |
==========================================================================
Outputs & filters:
-------------------------------------
  0 - output([INTERNAL_FUNCTION(A.c1, A.c2, A.c3, A.c4, B.c1, B.c2, B.c3, B.c4)]), filter(nil), rowset=256
  1 - output([INTERNAL_FUNCTION(A.c1, A.c2, A.c3, A.c4, B.c1, B.c2, B.c3, B.c4)]), filter(nil), rowset=256
      dop=2
